$ Power Query M formula language standard library: File.Contents
@ File.Contents

`File.Contents(filename)` returns the content of `filename` as `binary`.

The following function reads a text file:
code {
let
   readTextFile = (filename) => → Microsoft/Power-Query/M-formula/standard-library/Text/FromBinary[Text.FromBinary](File.Contents(filename))
in
   readTextFile
code }

sa:
  The Power Query → Microsoft/Power-Query/M-formula/standard-library
